reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Light Weight for Traveling
reviews.reviewText: Our objective was to be able to put things away in small bags as separators but not have luggage.As of today 1/10/23 we have not traveled with yet, but will be within a month. We do cruises or fly to destinations and these will make it easier for us to get through security quicker too. Everything separated but in 1 or 2 bags each (Travel light). We bought 2 different colors (White & Blue) for when we travel.So I have already tried prelim using the bags by packing for our next trip in a few weeks and here is my results:Good:1. They are collapsible which means less storage room needed (When emptied, they store in the luggage small side pockets. This is convenient.2. If I have a excursion, I can fill 1 small bag for the outing and not have to carry all the other bags. It can hold the phones, sunglasses, hats or whatever I need it to do. And when using the items...the bag folds up into my pocket. (this was planned this way)3. Costs - There are all kinds of bags to buy but these were a great deal for the price.4. Zippers - Not a large zipper, so they fold up out of the way.5. Lightweight and Thin - It so is light weight that my IPhone cover weighs more than the bag.6. Keeps my stuff from getting wet in rain or snow.Cons -1. They kept changing shipping dates - Not manufactures fault but it was late. 2 different shipments but ordered at the exact same time and they were in stock. Ugg2. Not sure yet on durability - this will be tested during our trips. The lining is not support thick so I would not put anything sharp in it. I am ok with this but others may not be.3. Came completely rolled up (I will up load the pictures later.Overall - I would give this a 9 our of 10 (because I have not tested on the road. Only practicing packing at home to see how it would function).For the price this purchase was worth it because it "fits" our needs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars A Little Small
reviews.reviewText: While these compress very well, I found them to be a little on the thin/flimsy side. The material was always getting caught and jamming the zipper. Found a way around it by putting my fingers under the zipper when zipping. Still, it was annoying, especially when I was in a hurry. They were a little small for my needs, but fit into my 26" bag easily. I'll use them, but I wouldn't purchase again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great packing tool
reviews.reviewText: I travel a lot for leisure and used these on a recent trip. Great packing tool. My suitcase fit way more than normal and kept everything organized. I was able to take sufficient clothes shoes and toiletries for a 4 day trip in a small suitcase. I used the large one for pants, sweaters, and dresses. The middle one had all of my pj's, socks, and Langere and the small handled all toiletries. There was plenty of room for souvenirs and shoes in my case...even a leather coat. Love these.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I’m a believer!
reviews.reviewText: It took me a while to decide which packing cubes to buy and I made the right choice. The fabric is thin, yet durable and I am absolutely astonished at how much fits in one cube! I did not use compression because I needed to use all of the space of the bag and didn’t want to break the zipper, but this will make my packing SO MUCH BETTER! Note: the items listed in the picture are for an average-sized 7 year old. He could easily carry all of his clothes in a backpack with room to spare (but I won’t make him). These are a game-changer.
